                  rdfs:comment """TODO: The definition has to be refined. 
TODO: Write axioms based on the definition"""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "quasi-static (DC) characterization of magnetic properties"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Quasi-static (DC) characterization is a magnetic properties analyzing process for soft magnetic sheet materials which aims to determine a static magnetic curve of the tested material. During the test, the current in the primary winding is changed slowly, thus the frequency of a magnetic field remains low, i.e., below 0.01 Hz. The output of the quasi-static characterization of magnetic properties  is a static B-H curve, which  provides information on hysteresis loss Ph, saturation induction Bsat, coercivity Hc, remanence Br, and maximum permeability µmax. During DC characterization primarily domain wall motion and pinning effects play role."@en ;
                  skos:example "Measurement of hysteresis losses; measurement of saturation magnetic induction at specified maximal magnetic field, e.g., 5000 A/m."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011
noes:NOES_0000011 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000829 ,
