                                    owl:someValuesFrom noes:NOES_0000184
                                  ] ;
                  rdfs:label "magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester"@en ;
                  skos:definition "magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester is an assay for determining magnetic properties of soft mangetic materials, where magnetic field H is applied to a single sheet."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014
noes:NOES_0000014 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( co:PMD_0000829
                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                               owl:onProperty obo:RO_0000057 ;
                                                               owl:someValuesFrom noes:NOES_0000185
                                                             ]
                                                           ) ;
                                        rdf:type owl:Class
                                      ] ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000829 ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty obo:RO_0000057 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom noes:NOES_0000185
                                  ] ;
                  rdfs:label "magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core is an assay for determing magnetic properties of soft magnetic materials, where the sample has closed wound ring core shape. As the ring shape does not have any air gaps or joint losses, this testing procedure provides information on most intrinsic material properties."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015
noes:NOES_0000015 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf noes:NOES_0000023 ;
                  rdfs:comment "Cold rolling is a rolling process which aims to reduce thickness of a metallic sheet. Cold rolling takes place at room temperature."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "cold rolling"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016
noes:NOES_0000016 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf noes:NOES_0000023 ;
                  rdfs:comment "Hot rolling is a rolling process which aims to reduce the thickness of a sheet material. Hot rolling  takes place at temperatures above alloy's recrystallization temperature."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "hot rolling"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017
noes:NOES_0000017 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000015 ;
                  rdfs:comment "Occurence of magnetic flux  is a process that (realizes??) responds with magnetic flux in the material when some magnetic field is applied."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "occurence of magnetic flux"@en ;
                  owl:deprecated "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018
noes:NOES_0000018 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000015 ;
                  rdfs:comment """follows  Arrhenius equation.
Has part grain growth and recovery."""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "recrystallization"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Recrystallization is a naturally occuring process which occurs in metallic materials and during which deformed grains are replaced by new defect-free grains. Recrystallization is a thermally activated process, i.e., it requires sufficiently high temperatures for the process to occur. Thus, recrystallization is a process which is part of annealing heat treatment."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019
noes:NOES_0000019 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000015 ;
                  rdfs:label "recovery"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Recovery is a naturally occuring process which occurs in metallic materials and during which the reduction of stored deformation energy in grains occurs due to the removal and rearragement of crystal structure defects (dislocations). Recovery is a part of recrystallization process, thus it is a thermally activated process, which occurs during annealing heat treatment."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020
noes:NOES_0000020 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000015 ;
                  rdfs:label "grain growth"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Grain growth is a process which occurs in polycrystalline materials. The driving force of grain growth is reduction of the interal energy via reduction of the total grain boundary. Grain growth is a thermally activated process which occurs after recovery and (primary) recrystallization."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021
noes:NOES_0000021 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0025009 ;
                  rdfs:label "domain wall motion"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Domain wall motion is a naturally occuring process which occurs in ferromagnetic materials due to the external stimulus such as applied magnetic field."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022
noes:NOES_0000022 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0025009 ;
                  rdfs:label "domain wall pinning"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Domain wall pinning is a naturally occuring process which occurs in ferromagnetic materials when domain wall montion is temporally inhibited due to an energy barrier."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023
noes:NOES_0000023 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000649 ;
                  rdfs:comment "Rolling is a shaping process in which material is passed through under a roll with the goal of reducing the thickness of a semi-finished object. After rolling the mateiral deformed microstructure, which is characterized by elongated defomed grains, high dislocation density, high internal strains, and preferred grain orientation."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "rolling"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024
noes:NOES_0000024 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000906 ;
                  rdfs:comment "The defintion has potential"@en ;
                  rdfs:label "strip-casting"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Strip-casting is a primary shaping from fluid state process for metals and alloys. During Strip-casting the melt flows between two rolls resulting in the strip."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025
noes:NOES_0000025 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000650 ;
                  rdfs:label "Schmieden"@de ,
                             "forging"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Forging is a pressure forming process of metals and alloys. During forging the material is heated to forging temperature and formed to the desired form using either hammers and anvils or heat-resistant upper and lower dies."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026
noes:NOES_0000026 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000779 ;
                  rdfs:label "normalizing"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Normalizing is a heat treatment process which aims to create uniform grain structure and improve toughness of an alloy. During normalizing the material is heated above its critical temperature, kept at this temperature for a period of time, and then cooled in the air."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027
noes:NOES_0000027 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000779 ;
                  rdfs:label "annealing"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Annealing is a heat treatment process which aims to soften an alloy and relieve internal stresses. The material is heated above its critical termperature at which recrystallization occurs. After holding the material at the temperature, it is cooled in a slow and controlled way usually inside an oven."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031
noes:NOES_0000031 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf noes:NOES_0000001 ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty obo:BFO_0000050 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom noes:NOES_0000094
                                  ] ;
                  rdfs:label "longitudinal direction"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Longitudinal direction is a rolled sheet direction along the dimension in which an anisotropic material property is measured. Longitudinal direction might be parallel to the rolling or transversal direction of a rolled material, and it is always normal to the rolling direction."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032
noes:NOES_0000032 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf co:PMD_0000625 ;
                  rdfs:label "scanning electron microscopy"@en ;
                  rdfs:seeAlso "https://www.thermofisher.com/de/de/home/materials-science/learning-center/applications/sem-tem-difference.html" ;
                  skos:altLabel "SEM"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) is a type of electron microscopy where a focused beam of electrons scans the surface of an object. An image is created by detecting electrons reflected from the surface. Thus, SEM provides information on the surface and composition of the sample."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033
noes:NOES_0000033 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( noes:NOES_0000001
                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                               owl:onProperty co:PMD_0000077 ;
                                                               owl:hasValue noes:NOES_0000028
                                                             ]
                                                           ) ;
                                        rdf:type owl:Class
                                      ] ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf noes:NOES_0000001 ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty obo:BFO_0000050 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom noes:NOES_0000094
                                  ] ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty noes:NOES_0000068 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom noes:NOES_0000036
                                  ] ;
                  rdfs:comment """TODO: 
1. Refine definition
2. Maybe remove the categorical values""" ;
                  rdfs:label "rolling direction"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Rolling direction is a rolled sheet direction that is specified by rolling direction (RD)."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034
noes:NOES_0000034 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf noes:NOES_0000153 ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty obo:RO_0009006 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom co:PMD_0020112
                                  ] ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty obo:RO_0009006 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom cryo:CRYO_0000042
                                  ] ;
                  rdfs:label "electron backscatter diffraction"@en ;
                  rdfs:seeAlso "Electron Backscatter Diffraction (EBSD) is a SEM based technique for characterizing  material's local microstructure. EBSD provides an information about phases and their distribution in the material, grain structure, grain size, grain boundary, texture  (crystallographic orientation of individual grains), and local strain variation."@en ,
                               "https://www.ebsd.com/ebsd-explained/what-is-ebsd" ;
                  skos:altLabel "EBSD"@en .


