###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041
noes:NOES_0000041 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000141 ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty obo:BFO_0000051 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom obo:BFO_0000140
                                  ] ,
                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                    owl:onProperty noes:NOES_0000074 ;
                                    owl:someValuesFrom obo:BFO_0000040
                                  ] ;
                  rdfs:comment "Note that intrinsic reference frame is \"grounded into\" the material entity, i.e., it moves with it, and if material entity ceases to exist so will its intrinsic reference frame."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "intrinsic reference frame"@en ;
                  skos:definition "Intrinsic reference frame is an immaterial entity  which is geometric basis of some material entity, e.g., material or an object. Intrinsic reference frame has parts continuant fiat boundaries, e.g., specific directions or planes which uniquely define this reference frame."@en .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042
