                  rdfs:comment """Note on a crystal structure: 
theoretically possible in both bcc and fcc because <100> are the same types of directions
practically lambda fiber is not stable in fcc because of the slip systems"""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "λ-fibre grain orientation"@en ;
                  skos:altLabel "<100> || ND" ;
                  skos:definition "λ-fibre grain orientation is a type of grain orientation which is quality of polycrystal, i.e., several grains, oriented in the following way: <100> family of crystallographic directions are oriented parallel to the normal direction (ND) of a sheet material, i,e., normal to the rolling plane."@en .


